Do I need to read a book to learn to use Linux?
text:
I was reading askubuntu answers and everyone was like "just read online and ask help online". I did that for 1 month and what I've realized is that I am memorizing solutions rather than understanding them.

But I also realize that there'll be no books about ubuntu because they get outdated fast.

So, someone in linux forum recommended me this book.

https://rlworkman.net/howtos/rute/

can you recommend some good books about linux that will help me to use linux as a desktop use firstly.

Making portable Flutter desktop exe with Rust
text:
Lately we are migrating our desktop version from Sciter sdk to Flutter. To keep it portable, we need to wrap the flutter desktop app to one single exe. After some investigation, we decided to write our own wrapper with Rust, here we use brotli as the compressor and decompressor, it has very good compression ratio (comprable to xz, but obviously higer than gz), and very good depression speed (better than xz and gz).

https://github.com/rustdesk/rustdesk/tree/master/libs/portable
